As Floyd bore down on the U.S. coast, 2 million people were urged to leave their homes in Florida, Georgia and South Carolina.
President Clinton issued pre-emptive disaster declarations for Florida and Georgia.
At 2 p.m. EDT, Floyd was about 195 miles east-southeast of Palm Beach, or near Abaco in the Bahamas, and moving to the west-northwest at about 14 mph. A gradual turn toward the northwest was expected later today.
In northern Nassau, residents reported flooding a quarter-mile inland.
